Figure 6.1

Needs christ data set and a couple of linear models fitted

```r
p<-ggplot(christ, aes(x=ripdens, y=cwdbasal))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(se=FALSE, color=lc)+
  xlab(\Riparian density (x 100)\)+ylab(\CWD basal area\)+
  theme_qk()
# Add boxes
p1<-ggMarginal(p,size=20, type=\boxplot\)

#Residual plot
p2<-ggplot(christ.lm, aes(x = christ.lm$fitted.values, y = christ.lm$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc) +
  labs(x = \Predicted value\, y = \Residuals\)+
  theme_qk()

```r
p<-ggplot(christ, aes(x=lcabin, y=lcwd))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(se=FALSE, color=lc)+
  xlab("Log10 (cabin density+1)")+ylab("log10(CWD basal area)")+
  theme_qk()
#Add boxes
p1<-ggMarginal(p,size=20, type="boxplot")
#Residual plot
p2<-ggplot(christ3.lm, aes(x = christ3.lm$fitted.values, y = christ3.lm$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc) +
  labs(x = "Predicted value", y = "Residuals")+
  theme_qk()
f6_3a<-plot_spacer()+p1+plot_spacer()+p2+plot_layout(widths=c(0.001,1.2,0.05,1))
f6_3a

```r
giri <- read.csv(\data/giri.csv\)
my_sum <- giri %>%
  group_by(treat) %>%
  summarise( 
    n=n(),
    mean=mean(n.3.LC.PUFA),
    sd=sd(n.3.LC.PUFA)
  ) %>%
  mutate( se=sd/sqrt(n))
 my_sum$treat<-as.factor(my_sum$treat)
# Standard Error
f6_5<-ggplot(my_sum, aes(x=treat,y=mean)) +
  geom_bar(stat=\identity\, width=0.5, fill=lf, color=lc) +
  geom_errorbar( aes(x=treat, ymin=mean-se, ymax=mean+se),  colour=lc, alpha=0.9, size=1, width=0) +
  labs(x = \Amount of food added\, y = \n-3 LC-PUFA (mg/g\, 
       )+
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0,0))+      #Puts bars on flush x-axis, rather than floating
  theme_qk()
f6_5

medley <- read.csv(\data/medley.csv\)
medley.aov <- aov(diversity~zinc, data=medley)
# force zn into right order 
p1<-ggplot(medley, aes(x=fct_relevel(zinc, c(\BACK\, \LOW\, \MED\, \HIGH\)),y=diversity))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  xlab(\Zinc level\)+ylab(\Diatom diversity\)
#Residual plot
p2<-ggplot(medley.aov, aes(x = medley.aov$fitted.values, y = medley.aov$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc) +
  labs(x = \Predicted diversity (for each zinc level)\, y = \Residuals\, 
       )
f6_6<-p1 + p2 & theme_qk()
f6_6

serpulid <- read.csv(\data/serpulid.csv\)
serpulid$film <- factor(serpulid$film)
serpulid.aov <- aov(lserp~film, data=serpulid)
my_sum <- serpulid %>%
  group_by(film) %>%
  summarise( 
    n=n(),
    mean=mean(lserp),
    sd=sd(lserp)
  ) %>%
  mutate( se=sd/sqrt(n))
# Standard Error
f6_8<-ggplot(my_sum, aes(x=film,y=mean)) +
  geom_bar(stat=\identity\, width=0.5, fill=lf, color=lc) +
  geom_errorbar( aes(x=film, ymin=mean-se, ymax=mean+se),  colour=lc, alpha=0.9, size=1, width=0) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0,0))+
theme_qk()+
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(colour = \black\),
         )+
  labs(x = \\, y = \Log(serpulids)\, 
       )
f6_8

```r
```r
peakquinn <- read.csv(\data/peakquinn.csv\)
peakquinn$larea<-log10(peakquinn$area)
peakquinn$lspecies<-log10(peakquinn$species)
peakquinn$lindiv<-log10(peakquinn$indiv)
pq.lm<-lm(lspecies~larea, data=peakquinn)
pq2.lm<-lm(lindiv~larea, data=peakquinn)
pq3.lm<-lm(indiv~area,data=peakquinn)

p<-ggplot(peakquinn, aes(x=larea, y=lspecies))+
  geom_point(color=sc)+
  geom_smooth(method=\lm\, se=FALSE, color=lc)+
  xlab(\Log area\)+ylab(\Log no. species\)+
  theme_qk()
# Add marginal box plots
p1<-ggMarginal(p,size=20, type=\boxplot\)

# Residual plot
p2<-ggplot(pq.lm, aes(x = pq.lm$fitted.values, y = pq.lm$residuals)) +
  geom_point(color=sc) +
  geom_smooth(se=FALSE, colour=lc)+
  labs(x = \Predicted log no. species\, y = \Residuals\, 
       )+
  theme_qk()
